SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 75
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to recognize Hamblen County Mayor Bill Brittain
on the occasion of his retirement.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we specially recognize those estimable public servants who
have dedicated themselves to improving the quality of life for their fellow citizens; and
WHEREAS, Hamblen County Mayor Bill Brittain is one such estimable person who
evinces the greatest integrity and probity in all his chosen endeavors; and
WHEREAS, a longtime public servant, Mr. Brittain served as Mayor of Hamblen County
since his election in 2010, and he subsequently won reelection to that esteemed position since
that time; and
WHEREAS, he has taken his much-deserved retirement from Hamblen County
Government on October 1, 2024, following nearly thirty-one years of service to his community;
and
WHEREAS, throughout his distinguished tenure, Mayor Bill Brittain provided solid
leadership and thoughtful guidance for his fellow citizens; and
WHEREAS, among his many achievements in office, Mayor Brittain facilitated the safety
of Hamblen County citizens and stewarded the Hamblen County Justice Center Project, which
featured a new facility that opened this year; and
WHEREAS, prior to his service as Mayor of Hamblen County, Bill Brittain served as
County Trustee for Hamblen County, a position he held since 1994; and
WHEREAS, he attended Walters State Community College from 1976 to 1978 and
earned his Bachelor of Science degree in Communications from the University of Tennessee,
Knoxville in 1981; and
